<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 10 at 2:59PM MDT until July 10 at 3:15PM MDT by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 330 PM MDT
FOR NORTH CENTRAL WELD COUNTY...
At 258 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 6 miles northeast of
Grover, or 32 miles southwest of Kimball, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Grover and Pawnee Buttes.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
